# Python Standards (offie)

## Goals

- **Consistency**: Keep style and patterns consistent across modules.
- **Clarity**: Prefer readable, explicit code over clever one-liners.
- **Pragmatism**: Follow project rules over generic style advice when they differ.

## General Guidelines

- Prefer standard library and existing project utilities before adding new dependencies.
- Keep functions small and focused; extract helpers when logic becomes complex.
- Name modules, classes, and functions descriptively; avoid abbreviations that are not obvious.
- Favor pure functions where possible for core logic, and keep side effects at the edges.

